Complementary description of male sex. Similar to female in all characters given in the original description (
Vas 2023b
), except the following. Area basalis is barely separated from area superomedia in male (while these are distinctly separated in female), and second tergite is more elongate in male than in female, almost 2.0× as long as its apical width.
